txt.en: 'I think it is a city of Rohan. No city built by the hands of Men can hope to compare to those of the Elves, even in this passing Age. But it suffices as a place for them to live, if this is what they call living. I see no Art, I hear little Music. It seems to me these men of Rohan survive, but they do not live.\n\n'I have said nothing of this to any of them, of course. It might be considered impolite.'
What do you think of Cliving?
